# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# diffusion-q-learning.form — QAM (Q-learning with Adjoint Matching) grafted
#                            onto the learning engine the body already runs.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The field (2026-06): "Q-learning with Adjoint Matching" (Li & Levine,
# arXiv:2601.14234) reports the strongest current result for optimising an
# expressive diffusion / flow-matching policy against a Q-critic. Its whole
# contribution is to do this WITHOUT backpropagation through the multi-step
# denoising chain — that backprop is numerically unstable, so prior methods
# either threw the critic gradient away (reweighting, IDQL) or approximated it
# at a cost in expressivity. QAM uses ADJOINT MATCHING to turn the critic's
# action-gradient into a per-step regression objective that needs no chain
# unroll, yet is unbiased and fully expressive at the optimum.
#
# The recognition that makes this native here: the body's adjoint is ALREADY a
# forward gather. metabolic-learning.fk ships mtb-reverse — "backprop through
# gl-step IS gl-step over reversed edges" (band claim 512). So the thing QAM had
# to construct, this substrate has as a primitive. QAM reduces to: feed the
# critic's action-gradient ∇_aQ as the metabolic DELTA, and let mtb-reverse
# carry it through the policy. No new engine — one new critic + one tilt dial.
#
# LANES (CLAUDE.md discipline — kept separate):
#   [RUNS]   proven four-way (Go/Rust/TS/fkwu) by tests/diffusion-q-learning-band.fk → 255
#   [INFER]  architectural inference; falsifiable, not yet walked
# Unlike a pure design cell, the GRAFT here RUNS: the eight claims below are the
# proven band, not a sketch. What stays [INFER] is the SCALE-UP, named honestly.

(diffusion-q-learning

  (lineage
    (operator       metabolic-learning.form)    # pressure × frequency × angle × focus; mtb-reverse [RUNS]
    (gather         geometric-learning.form)    # gl-step; gl-bellman (the RL/value limb) [RUNS]
    (objective-kin  preference-learning.form)   # QAM = KTO's transform:"value" with a LEARNED critic [RUNS row family]
    (serve-while-improve champion-challenger.form)  # the offline→online loop — WIRED + proven: diffusion-q-cc.fk + band → 31 [RUNS]
    (mesh           federated-slices.form))      # many critics, deterministic slice-merge [RUNS]

  # ── 1. The proven graft — eight claims, four-way [RUNS: band → 255] ──
  # A one-hot context makes the policy params BE the action, so every weight is
  # exact in fp64. The critic Q(a) = 2·a0 + 1·a1 makes action 0 the higher value.
  (proven
    (free-backtrace   dql-grad-a recovers ∇_aQ = [2 1] by the ADJOINT (reversed-edge gather), no tape)
    (improve-ascends  one QAM step raises Q from 0 → 2.5 — the policy climbed the critic)
    (toward-argmax    the action moved to [1 0.5], a positive margin 0.5 onto the higher-Q action)
    (observer-gate    pressure(∇Q) at tolerance ⇒ params UNTOUCHED — a resolved action costs nothing)
    (bc-limit         q-focus 0 ⇒ the actor is PURE behaviour-clone (the λ→∞ limit), bit-identical to BC)
    (superposition    actor − BC = exactly q-focus·(critic credit) — one operator fired twice, additive)
    (td-bootstrap     the critic target r+γ·Q' = 2.5 matches the SHIPPED gl-bellman max-plus backup)
    (deep-adjoint     a TWO-layer policy gradient = the reference, by reversed gathers — the chain rule
                      with NO unrolled autograd tape: QAM's "no backprop through the chain", on our kernel))

  # ── 1b. Wired into a live loop — the offline→online promotion [RUNS: band → 31] ──
  # No longer an island: diffusion-q-cc.fk grafts dql-improve onto champion-challenger.
  # A served champion policy already reaches the target value (Q=2.5); a raw challenger
  # (Q=0) earns authority ONLY by the Q-tilt. dql-improve is the move that flips its trials
  # from losing to winning; cc-promote? is the gate. The coin stays gl-veq6 equality
  # (round-vs-round, fourth-arm safe) and the competition is champion-challenger's integer counts.
  (consumed-by-loop
    (raw-stays-behind   the un-improved challenger (Q=0) loses every trial → the champion keeps authority)
    (tilt-earns-it      a sufficient Q-tilt (focus 1/2, Q→2.5) reaches the champion → PROMOTED, authority flips)
    (trusted-window     a winning challenger on a SHORT window (< min-samples) is NOT promoted — earned, not lucky)
    (insufficient-tilt  a partial tilt (focus 1/8, Q→0.625) has not reached → still behind, not promoted)
    (kernel-earned-it   dql-improve raised the challenger's value 0 → 2.5, the champion's level, by the adjoint))

  # ── 2. The mapping — every QAM piece is a cell already here ──────────
  (mapping
    (diffusion-policy   [RUNS gather] the action is a recipe cell; ml-diffusion-model-flow denoise + mtb trains it)
    (critic-Q           [INFER, one new cell] value-as-gather: a gl/mtb learner over (state, action) edges;
                        target y = r + γ·min Q(s',a') — gl-bellman is that backup already four-way)
    (adjoint-matching   [RUNS] mtb-reverse — the critic's action-gradient pushed through the policy as a
                        forward reversed gather; mtb-credit is the per-step objective, mtb-unwrap the update)
    (q-tilt-row         [INFER row] π* ∝ μ_β·exp(Q/λ): a preference-learning row whose reference is the
                        LEARNED critic and whose pull is the adjoint-matched ∇Q. λ = the q-focus aperture)
    (bc-anchor          [RUNS] the diffusion behaviour-clone loss = the distillation descent; keeps in-support))

  # ── 3. Feature-set fit — what the asker named, where it lives ───────
  (features
    (cells-as-nodes  [RUNS] the action is a content-addressed recipe, not a float vector; the policy emits a NODE)
    (free-backtrace  [RUNS] mtb-reverse is the adjoint as a reversed gather; content-addressing adds attribution)
    (smart-branching [RUNS] branch-choice-order.form — learned ordering of choice branches from witnessed receipts)
    (fast-fail       [RUNS] attention-as-CHOICE/FAIL/CUT/STOP (form-native-llm); a wrong action is O(1) to abandon)
    (mesh-learning   [RUNS] federated-slices slice-merge — many critics consolidate deterministically))

  # ── 4. Where the substrate is STRONGER than dense Diffusion-QL ──────
  (beyond-port
    (sparse-for-free  the action is a cell; irrelevant branches FAIL/CUT at O(1) — sparsity QAM pays float for is native)
    (federated-critics each cell runs its own QAM loop; slice-merge reaches the SAME numbers, which float-averaging can't)
    (traceable-adjoint every Q-update is a content-addressed delta with Blueprint provenance — cheap AND attributable))

  # ── 5. The fourth-arm float idiom (a lesson this graft re-proved) ───
  # The band's first cut diverged on fkwu (185 vs 255). Root cause: raw float
  # gt/lt and round-vs-raw-large-int-literal box differently on the fourth
  # kernel than on the three walkers. The fix is the body's standing discipline,
  # held here too: compare floats ONLY through the verdict lens gl-veq6
  # (round-vs-round). Never a raw gt/lt and never (eq (gl-r6 x) <large-int>) at
  # the verdict level — both pass three-way and hide a fourth-arm divergence.

  # ── 6. The gaps (the next stones, named — not built ahead of need) ──
  (gaps
    (GAP-Q1  [INFER] form/form-stdlib/diffusion-q-learning.fk carries the seam recipes (dql-q, dql-grad-a,
             dql-improve, dql-actor, dql-td-target, dql-backstep). The next stone is mtb-settle-style
             ITERATION: a critic trained by repeated gl-bellman backups to a fixed point, the policy
             improved to convergence, the whole loop one band)
    (GAP-Q2  [INFER] the q-tilt as a first-class preference-learning row (reference:"critic", transform:
             "q-adjoint"), so auto-research can evolve it alongside the DPO/KTO family it extends)
    (GAP-Q3  [INFER] the mesh: federated critics over slice-merge, each cell's runtime error feeding its
             short-term plasticity, only settled long-term value shared — QAM inside mesh-active-inference))
  # (the offline→online champion-challenger loop landed — see §1b, diffusion-q-cc.fk + band → 31)

  (invariant
    (graft-runs   the math graft is PROVEN four-way (255), not asserted; QAM's no-backprop-through-chain
                  promise is re-earned on our kernel by the two-layer adjoint claim)
    (one-engine   no second native path — the recipe that proves four-way is the recipe that crystallises
                  to native asm; the critic and the policy are both the one gl/mtb gather over edge data)
    (scale-honest the band is strange-minimal (2 actions, one-hot context); real width + the iterated loop
                  are [INFER] stones, taken when an ask needs them, never built ahead of need)))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to run / how to query
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   # Prove the band four-way (from form/):
#   ./validate.sh form-stdlib/geometric-learning.fk form-stdlib/metabolic-learning.fk \
#                 form-stdlib/diffusion-q-learning.fk \
#                 form-stdlib/tests/diffusion-q-learning-band.fk
#   # → 255, fourth arm four-way (fkwu + pre-flattened tables)
#
#   # Structural queries once ingested (auto on merge to main):
#   coh substrate form "?equivalent @recipe(dql-improve)"
